		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's not, it filled the need for color TV which was backwards compatible with black &amp; white TV before any others. It's just old. Nowadays (interlaced games) you can play a game in composite and hardly see the difference between it and component/RGB. Anyways, I would take the low color bandwidth of NTSC over the flickeryness of a 50Hz set anyway. And it's all a moot point since the best games are all developed for 525 lines / 60Hz.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
