	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />NTSC crams more than one signal together, so it acts sort of like digital where there is a hard limit to resolution. With RGB, there's no design limit to resolution, since each signal is carried separately. It's not that NTSC was a crappy standard, it's that we haven't moved forward fast enough; the damn thing is over 40 years old! I recently got a TV with an S-Video input and that is so much clearer looking than composite looks on the thing from the same system, so things did move forward (and of course component is to die for).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


